[1] Samoa (Upolo Island)
Date: Tue 20 Mar 2012
Source: Pacific Islands News Association (PINA) [edited]
http://www.pina.com.fj/index.php?p=pacnews&m=read&o=9600585394f6800c0e748887cfe742

Typhoid death in Samoa prompts action
----------------------
The death of a one-year-old baby from a village in Upolu from typhoid has sparked the Red Cross Samoa into action.

The Red Cross conducted a hygienic assessment in Aele last week and is now supporting the villagers by providing them with soap and clothes to ensure the families are protected.

The group are also responding to several cases of typhoid in Malie, Upolu, with help from Rotary Samoa, Samoa Water Authority and other NGOs.

Nine members of one family in Malie had typhoid.

