******
[2] Christmas Island
Date: Tue 28 Feb 2012
Source: Herald Sun [edited]
http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/more-news/boat-arrivals-at-christmas-island-have-typhoid/story-fn7x8me2-1226283285256


Two asylum seekers have been diagnosed with typhoid, putting Christmas Island staff and inmates under watch. The 2 men arrived on different boats over the past week.

One has been admitted to hospital on the mainland [Australia] while the other is in isolation on the island, an immigration department spokeswoman said yesterday, 27 Feb 2012.

She said staff and inmates who had come in contact with the pair were being monitored for signs of the disease, contracted by contaminated food or water and spread by bacteria. Despite other diseases being picked up over the past 20 months in asylum seekers, including syphilis, hepatitis B, and C and active tuberculosis, it is the 1st time typhoid has been diagnosed in some time.

A total of 25 vessels have arrived since December 2011 with 2068 people on board, smashing arrival records set in previous summers.

