[The introduction of _S. enterica_ serotype Typhi into areas with adequate sewage control such as Australia does not represent a threat to the general population. - Mod.LL]

[Christmas Island can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at http://healthmap.org/r/1*jB. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

******
[3] Fiji (Western)
Date: Wed 21 Mar 2012
Source: The Fiji Times [edited]
http://www.fijitimes.com/story.aspx?id=196547


There has been a substantial decrease in typhoid cases at Koroboya Village and Naitasiri Village of Ba [Western division], says the Ministry of Health. Spokesman Peni Namotu said there had been no new cases of typhoid since the inception of the Public Health Emergency Regulation in February 2012.

So far, health teams have recorded and treated 15 cases of typhoid at the 2 villages. "We have noticed a great improvement of sanitary conditions at the villages," Mr Namotu said.

"Right now, our health officers are working on further improving their sanitary conditions and also change their mind-set about healthy living. Changing people's way of thinking is very important because when our teams move out, we want them to continue living in a clean environment," he said.

[Byline: Repeka Nasiko]

